.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"2\" title=\"Day 2: Namchi-Pelling\"]Visit  Char Dham in Namchi and in the Afternoon, take the mesmerising route to Pelling, appreciating the beauty of this natural wonder.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"3\" title=\"Day 3: Pelling\"]This day we visit the beautiful Kanchenjunga Falls, Khecheopalri Lake and Pemayangtse Monastery. A quiet and serene pathway takes you through sometimes steep and winding roads of the hills.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"4\" title=\"Day 4: Pelling\"] Trek for around 3 kms in morning to see one of the most beautiful Monastery and some mesmerising views on the way. This is a special day as today we will spend some memorable time in an NGO with some adorable kids. And later walk upto Rabdanse Ruins to enjoy the spectacular views of the Kanchendzong hill ranges.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"5\" title=\"Day 5: Pelling-Darjeeling\"]After breakfast, we will leave for Darjeeling- ‘The Queen of Hills’. On the way we will see Tea farms and visit a Japanese temple. We spend the evening relaxing and everyone is encouraged to explore the locality.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"6\" title=\"Day 6: Darjeeling\"]Visit Tiger Hill early morning situated at an altitude of 8000 feet for an amazing view of Mount Kanchenjunga and then some sight seeing of Darjeeling including Himalayan Mountaineering Institute and Darjeeling Zoo. In the evening we’ll enjoy a farewell group dinner and one last night out together before we part ways at the end of this most memorable trip.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"7\" title=\"Day 7: Darjeeling-Bagdogra Airport\"]Time to bid adieu. Check out from hotel and transfer to Bagdogra airport or New Jalpaiguri Railway Station via taxi for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item]<strong>End of this memorable tour.</strong>\r\n\r\n[/timeline]\";}i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:20