er_mask\";s:7:\"default\";}'),(4347,1844,'tour_tabs_meta','a:2:{s:10:\"tour_badge\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"tabs\";a:2:{i:0;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:9:\"Itinerary\";s:7:\"content\";s:2786:\"[timeline][timeline_item item_number=\"1\" title=\"Day 1: Delhi to Mcleodganj\"]Take an AC Volvo Bus from Kashmiri Gate, New Delhi to Mcleodganj. It will be an overnight journey. Reporting time is 06:30 PM.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"2\" title=\"Day 2: Mcleodganj\"]Reach hotel at Mcleodganj. Entire day will be to explore the Mcleodganj town and Dharamshala town. You can also visit the famous HPCA Cricket Stadium\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"3\" title=\"Day 3: Mcleodganj to Triund\"]Trek from Mcleodganj to Triund (2875 metres / 9 KM ). After breakfast, we say hello to our Triund trek guide – an experienced, reliable and English speaking guide who will help you trek up 2900 meters, all the way to the stunning Triund.\r\n\r\nThe Triund Trek trail starts from the colourful market of Mcleodganj and passes through the quaint village of Dharamkot. From Galu Devi Temple, the Triund trek trail takes you through the refreshing forests of Oak, Rhododendron and Deodhar. The first few kilometres of this trek is graded as easy and the last stretch is a bit of a push- but for the delicious views that await us, it’s completely worth it.\r\n\r\nAwaiting you at the summit of this Triund trek, is a large green (or white if it has snowed!) pasture that offers panoramic views of the Bhagsu village, Mcleodganj, the Dharamsala valley and distant views of Shivalik hills and the plains of Kangra valley.\r\n\r\nHere, we live our dreams of camping in the wilderness of the Himalayas. We set camp with our warm and waterproof tents at strategic position where you can have the best overnight views and at the same time, you are least affected by the mountain wind. Eat delicious and freshly cooked food as you sing to the warm crackling music of the bonfire and create memories that would last a lifetime.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"4\" title=\"Day 4: Triund to Mcleodganj\"]On the second day of the Triund Trek, wake up to this sight: The massive Dhauladhars on one side, the vast Kangra Valley on the other. As the sun kisses the Himalayan peaks, the snow glows orange and we bet that’s surely one of the best good-mornings you’ve ever had.\r\n\r\nAfter breakfast at 10,000+ feet, start walking back to Mcleodganj. However this time, weather permitting, you will take a hidden path – a trail not many trekkers are aware, and will pass through a quaint patch of wilderness, before you descend into Bhagsu, explore the beautiful waterfall and then come down to Mcleodganj.\r\n\r\nIn the night we will take a bus back to New Delhi and end our beautiful journey.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"5\" title=\"Day 5: Reach Delhi\"]We will reach Delhi by Morning 08 AM.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item]<strong>End of this memorable tour.</strong>\r\n\r\n[/timeline]\";}i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Terms and Conditions\";s:7:\"content\";s:911:\"Please note: if there is a lot of rain / snow at the summit, the guide will give you an option of switching to staying at a shared dorm at Triund. However, the cost of this is not included in the package and is subject to availability.\r\n<ul style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Cancellation policy:</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n 	<li>75% of your booking amount will be refunded, if you cancel your participation before 45 days of the tour date.</li>\r\n 	<li>50% of your booking amount will be refunded, if you cancel your participation before 30 days of the tour date.</li>\r\n 	<li>25% of your booking amount will be refunded, if you cancel your participation before 15 days of the tour date.</li>\r\n 	<li>No refund afterwards.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For more information you can also drop us an email at: info@yourholidayagent.com, Call us at: +91 9731587004</p>\";}}}'),(4348,1844,'_tax_status','taxable'),(4349,1844,'_tax_class',''),(4350,1844,'slide_template','default'),(4352,1844,'_product_version','2.6.14'),(4353,1844,'_variable_tour','no'),(4354,1844,'_vc_post_settings','a:1:{s:10:\"vc_grid_id\";a:0:{}}'),(4355,1844,'_edit_lock','1491942187:1'),(4356,1844,'_edit_last','1'),(4357,1844,'_product_image_gallery','1855,1854,1853,1852,1851,1850,1849,1848,1847,1846,1845'),(4358,1844,'_thumbnail_id','1850'),(4359,1844,'_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs','1'),(4361,1844,'_wp_old_slug','darjeeling-queen-of-hills'),(4362,1844,'_wpas_skip_15949937','1'),(4363,1844,'_wpas_skip_16120684','1'),(4365,1845,'_wp_attached_file','camps-triund-trekking.jpg'),(4366,1845,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:5:{s:5:\"width\";i:2048;s:6:\"height\";i:1366;s:4:\"file\";s:25:\"camps-triund-trekking.jpg\";s:5:\"sizes\";a:7:{s:9:\"thumbnail\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:33:\"camps-triund-trekking-150x150.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:150;s:6:\"height\";i:150;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:6:\"medium\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:33:\"camps-triund-trekking-300x200.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:300;s:6:\"height\";i:200;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:12:\"medium_large\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:33:\"camps-triund-trekking-768x512.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:768;s:6:\"height\";i:512;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:5:\"large\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:34:\"camps-triund-trekking-1024x683.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:1024;s:6:\"height\";i:683;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:14:\"shop_thumbnail\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:33:\"camps-triund-trekking-180x152.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:180;s:6:\"height\";i:152;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:12:\"shop_catalog\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:33:\"camps-triund-trekking-531x354.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:531;s:6:\"height\";i:354;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:11:\"shop_single\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:33:\"camps-triund-trekking-600x505.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:600;s:6:\"height\";i:505;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\