lace in Ladakh. Before Leh, Shey used to be the capital of Ladakh. After Shey, lets head to Shanti stupa followed by old and beautiful Leh palace.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"3\" title=\"Day 3: Nubra Valley via Khardungla Pass (5602 Mt)\"]Nubra is a high altitude cold desert, the land of sand dunes and two humped  bactrian camels. This day we will cross the world’s highest motor able pass- Khardungla. Overnight stay at Samoor in Swiss tents.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"4\" title=\"Day 4: Samoor to Pangong Lake\"]Pangong Lake- where the famous 3 Idiots movie was filmed- is a high grassland lake at a height of 4350 Mt and extends from India to China. You can see China from the Indian side of this lake. This lake freezes completely during winters. Overnight stay in camps.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"5\" title=\"Day 5: Pangong to Leh via Changla Pass\"]This day we go back to Leh via Changla Pass. Changla Pass is the third highest motor able road in the world. A quiet and serene pathway takes you through sometimes steep and winding roads of the hills.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"6\" title=\"Day 6: Leh- local sight seeing\"]Visit Magnetic Hill, Hall of fame, Gurudwara Pathar Sahib and Confluence of Zanskar and Indus river. This is almost a spiritual sight where two completely different coloured entities merge together and yet remain separate and choose to flow harmoniously in a common direction. The difference in colours of the waters of the two merging rivers is interesting to see.[/timeline_item]\r\n\r\n[timeline_item item_number=\"7\" title=\"Day 7: Drop to the Airport\"]Time to bid adieu. With truckload of awesome memories to relish for the rest of our lives, today we say goodbye to Leh. Check out from the guest house and transfer to the airport for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item]\r\n\r\n<strong>End of this memorable tour.</strong>\r\n\r\n[/timeline]\";}i:1;a:2