new roman\', times, serif\">Ways to reach your destination – Singapore is well connected by land, air and water too.</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\">Food – Chinese, Indian, Indonesian. It is very diverse!!</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\"><u>Some other facts:</u></span></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\">Singapore is commonly known as the lion city</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\">It houses the famous Merlion</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\">Chewing gums are not allowed in this country</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 18pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\">Places to visit and things to do in Singapore</span></strong></span>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif;font-size: 14pt\"><strong>Sentosa Island</strong> – Our top pick in Singapore is Sentosa. This small island is a popular getaway for tourists and one of the most happening places in South East Asia. Famous for its 3 beaches- Siloso, Palawan, and Tanjong beach- this is a perfect destination for de-stressing, and exciting parties.</span><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1627\" src=\"http://roamingclan.com/wp-content/uploads/Tanjong_Beach_in_Sentosa.jpg\" alt=\"group-tours-singapore\" width=\"517\" height=\"388\" /></span><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif;font-size: 14pt\"><strong>2.  A Visual Treat, the Merlion: </strong>The Merlion is Singapore’s mascot and has the head of a lion and the body of a fish. There are 7 Merlion statues in Singapore, however only 5 are recognized by the Singapore Tourism Board. </span><span style=\"font-size: 8pt\"><a href=\"http://roamingclan.com/tours/singapore-on-a-shoestring-group-trip/\">Singapore on a Shoestring Group Trip</a></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1638 size-large\" src=\"http://roamingclan.com/wp-content/uploads/singapore-travel-1024x354.jpg\" alt=\"best things to do in singapore, singapore group tours\" width=\"748\" height=\"259\" /></span>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif;font-size: 14pt\"><strong>3. Clarke Quay and </strong><strong>Riverside</strong> : This festival village dedicated to good times, combining dining, shopping and a heritage inspired Disney-style adventure ride. Over Clarke Quay is Attica, famous for its outrageous parties.</span></p>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1639\" src=\"http://roamingclan.com/wp-content/uploads/singapore-travel-fun.jpg\" alt=\"just bucket list things, hidden secrets of singapore\" width=\"631\" height=\"265\" /></span>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\"><strong> 4. The Universal Studios</strong>: Visit the most wowed upon place ever! The Sights, Games, Shows and Rides in this place leave you awestruck and make this the best part of your trip to Singapore.</span></p>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1640\" src=\"http://roamingclan.com/wp-content/uploads/singapore-group-travel-1024x733.jpg\" alt=\"best places to visit while in singapore, bucket list things, just travel things\" width=\"535\" height=\"383\" /></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 10pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\">Is Singapore in your bucket list? Check out this exciting 4Nights/5 Days group t