wp-image-1627 \" src=\"http://roamingclan.com/wp-content/uploads/Tanjong_Beach_in_Sentosa.jpg\" alt=\"group-tours\" width=\"517\" height=\"388\" />\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;font-family: \'comic sans ms\', sans-serif\">A Visual Treat, the Merlion</span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;font-family: \'comic sans ms\', sans-serif\">The Merlion is Singapore’s mascot and has the head of a lion and the body of a fish. There are 7 Merlion statues in Singapore, however only 5 are recognized by the Singapore Tourism Board.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-1638 size-large aligncenter\" src=\"http://roamingclan.com/wp-content/uploads/singapore-travel-1024x354.jpg\" alt=\"singapore-travel\" width=\"748\" height=\"259\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;font-family: \'comic sans ms\', sans-serif\">Clarke Quay</span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;font-family: \'comic sans ms\', sans-serif\">Riverside festival village dedicated to good times, combining dining, shopping and a heritage inspired Disney-style adventure ride. Over Clarke Quay is Attica, famous for its outrageous parties.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1639 \" src=\"http://roamingclan.com/wp-content/uploads/singapore-travel-fun.jpg\" alt=\"singapore-travel-fun\" width=\"631\" height=\"265\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;font-family: \'comic sans ms\', sans-serif\">Visit the most wowed upon place ever! The Universal Studios!</span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;font-family: \'comic sans ms\', sans-serif\">The Sights, Games, Shows and Rides in this place leave you awestruck and make this the best part of your trip to Singapore.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1640 \" src=\"http://roamingclan.com/wp-content/uploads/singapore-group-travel-1024x733.jpg\" alt=\"singapore-group-travel\" width=\"535\" height=\"383\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;font-family: \'comic sans ms\', sans-serif\">Singapore Zoo and Night Safari</span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;font-family: \'comic sans ms\', sans-serif\">The Singapore Zoo is a must-see. It’s an open-air zoo, which is great because animals aren’t locked up in tiny cages</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1641 size-full\" src=\"http://roamingclan.com/wp-content/uploads/singapore-travel-group-zoo.jpg\" alt=\"singapore-travel-group-zoo\" width=\"498\" height=\"354\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;font-family: \'comic sans ms\', sans-serif\">Experience the beauty and delicacies of China Town</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 18pt;font-family: \'comic sans ms\', sans-serif\"> -The Hong Kong Temple</span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;font-family: \'comic sans ms\', sans-serif\">The Hong Kong temple was made from the finest materials and best craftsmen that China had to offer around the time of its construction in the 1840s. The refreshed Chinatown Food Street celebrates the assembly of specialty dishes from main Chinese dialects and the different races in Singapore</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1643 \" src=\"http://roamingclan.com/wp-content/uploads/Singapore-temple-travel-e1480950249217.jpg\" alt=\"singapore-temple-travel\" width=\"429\" height=\"412\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;font-family: \'comic sans ms\', sans-serif\">Eat in Little India</span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;font-family: \'comic sans ms\', sans-serif\">Here you get interesting snacks, great vegetables, and oh-so-awesome food! This place has a large number of eating joints which offer authentic delicacies from India at very economical prices</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1644 \" src=\"http://roamingclan.com/wp-content/uploads/singapore-travel-tour-food.jpg\" alt=\"singapore-travel-tour-food\" width=\"566\" height=\"318\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><s