dth=\"631\" height=\"265\" /></span>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\"><strong> 4. The Universal Studios</strong>: Visit the most wowed upon place ever! The Sights, Games, Shows and Rides in this place leave you awestruck and make this the best part of your trip to Singapore.</span></p>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1640\" src=\"http://roamingclan.com/wp-content/uploads/singapore-group-travel-1024x733.jpg\" alt=\"best places to visit while in singapore, bucket list things, just travel things\" width=\"535\" height=\"383\" /></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 10pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\">Is Singapore in your bucket list? Check out this exciting 4Nights/5 Days group trip to Singapore from 25th January 2017 to 29th January 2017. Only for the young and lively. </span></strong><a href=\"http://roamingclan.com/tours/singapore-on-a-shoestring-group-trip/\">Singapore on a Shoestring Group Trip</a></span>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif;font-size: 14pt\"><strong>5.</strong> <strong>Singapore Zoo and Night Safari</strong>: The Singapore Zoo is a must-see. It’s an open-air zoo, which is great because animals aren’t locked up in tiny cages</span></p>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1641 size-full\" src=\"http://roamingclan.com/wp-content/uploads/singapore-travel-group-zoo.jpg\" alt=\"singapore group tour packages, your holiday agent\" width=\"498\" height=\"354\" /></span>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\"><strong>6. Experience the beauty and delicacies of China Town: </strong>Hong Kong Temple in china town is made from the finest materials and best craftsmen that China had to offer around the time of its construction in the 1840s. The refreshed Chinatown Food Street celebrates the assembly of specialty dishes from main Chinese dialects and the different races in Singapore</span></p>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1643\" src=\"http://roamingclan.com/wp-content/uploads/Singapore-temple-travel-e1480950249217.jpg\" alt=\"places to visit in singapore, things to do in singapore, experience travelling\" width=\"429\" height=\"412\" /></span>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif;font-size: 14pt\"><strong>7.</strong> <strong>Eat in Little India</strong>: Here you get interesting snacks, great vegetables, and oh-so-awesome food! This place has a large number of eating joints which offer authentic delicacies from India at very economical prices.</span></p>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1644\" src=\"http://roamingclan.com/wp-content/uploads/singapore-travel-tour-food.jpg\" alt=\"delicacies of singapore, best places to visit for food in singapore, tour packages\" width=\"566\" height=\"318\" /></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif;font-size: 14pt\"><strong>8. The Singapore River Cruise:</strong>  is one of the things most tourists enjoy. Taking a leisurely ride on the river cruise will take you past the landmarks of the Fullerton Hotel, Esplanade Singapore, The Merlion Park, Singapore Flyer and the latest attraction Marina Bay Sands Integrated Resort.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1646\" src=\"http://roamingclan.com/wp-content/uploads/singapore-cruise-travel-tour-group.jpg\" alt=\"hidden secrets of singapore, fun things to do in singapore, just travelling things\" width=\"604\" height=\"401\" /></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\">Is Singapore in your bucket list? Check out this exciting 4Nights/5 Days group trip to Singapore from 25th January 2017 to 29th January 2017. Only for the young and lively.</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://roamingclan.com/tours/singapore-on-a-shoestring-group-trip/\">Singapore on a Shoestring Group Trip</a>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\"><a href=\"http://roamingclan.com/tours/singapore-on-a-shoestring-group-trip/\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1653\" src=\"http://roamingclan.com/wp-content/uploads/singapore-group-tour.jpg\" alt=\"your holiday agent, group tour packages, singapore tour packages\" width=\"722\" height=\"481\" /></a></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Let us assure you that its not that typical touch and go tour. We explore, we party and we have made sure that you have enough time to interact with the locals and other travellers.  Save the dates!</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://roamingclan.com/tours/singapore-on-a-shoestring-group-trip/\">Singapore on a Shoestring Group Trip</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Singapore Mini Guide','','inherit','closed','closed','','1649-revision-v1','','','2016-12-07 14:29:48','2016-12-07 14:29:48','',1649,'http://roamingclan.com/1649-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1671,16,'2016-12-09 20:14:30','2016-12-09 20:14:30','<h1 style=\"text-align: center;padding-left: 30px\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times,serif;font-size: 36pt\"><strong>D</strong><strong>ressing</strong><strong> and Etiquettes -</strong></span></h1>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;padding-left: 30px\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times,serif;font-size: 36pt\"><strong>CAMBODIA STYLE </strong><strong>!</strong></span></h1>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times,serif\">Every country has its own culture, be it for food, clothing, songs, language, anything. Well Cambodia too has its unique culture which has been influenced by many neighbouring countries yet still has its own identity.</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times,serif\"> Due to the severe impact of its history on the culture, the traditional attires of Cambodia are very intriguing yet very simple.Cambodia cannot be termed as ‘backward’ but yes, it is still very reserved compared to many other countries in the world.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1812\" src=\"http://roamingclan.com/wp-content/uploads/Cambodian-Traditional-dress-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"748\" height=\"499\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"font-size: 18pt\">The local attire :</span></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;font-family: times new roman,times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt\">On daily basis, men in Cambodia wear t-shirts or shirts and full length trousers.</span></span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;font-family: times new roman,times,serif\">Whereas women wear blouses and knee length skirts called sampots.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt;font-family: times new roman,times,serif\">Tourists visit Cambodia from all over the globe and no matter what dress code works for their country, it is appreciated when they follow the rules of the Cambodian attire.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 24pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 18pt\">Cambodia and Women :</span>\r\n</strong></span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times,serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt\">Cambodia is a conserved country in terms of women wearing short skirts or shorts. </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt\"> </span></span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;font-family: times new roman,times,serif\">Women are also not allowed to be seen drinking in public.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1813\" src=\"http://roamingclan.com/wp-content/uploads/ideal-attire-when-visiting-cambodia.jpg\" alt=\"what-to-wear-in-Cambodia, things-to-do-in-Cambodia\" width=\"720\" height=\"960\" />\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;font-family: times new roman,times,serif\">In Cambodia, if a woman is seen with a man, he is expected to either be her husband or her fiancé.\r\nThese rules do not just imply to the local people, they are also meant for the tourists however, these rules are not so strictly enforced on them.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 18pt\"><strong>A humble advise to all:</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt;font-family: times new roman,times,serif\">Cambodian people are also kind of shy and take public display of affection to be quite offensive.</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times,serif\"> <span style=\"font-size: 12pt\"> That is why tourists are advised not to display too much affection in public as less as holding one’s hand if the person is of another gender. So roaming around holding your partner’s hand in a big no no in Cambodia!</span><em>\r\n</em></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 18pt\"><strong>Greeting ethics of Cambodia:</strong></span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times,serif\">Cambodians are also very simple people, absolutely in contrast to their complex food. Usually they warmly greet the people by shaking their hands. However,women greet others by ‘sompeyar’ which is more or less Indian ‘Namastey’.</span> <span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times,serif\">The women join their palms with fingers pointing up and palms at chest level with their heads bent a little in order to welcome somebody.</span></span><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times,serif\"><em>\r\n</em></span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times,serif\">Sompeyar is also done to pay respect to the monks and the lords.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1814\" src=\"http://roamingclan.com/wp-content/uploads/action-of-sompeyar-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"greeting-in-Cambodia, etiquettes-of-Cambodia, things-to-remember-when-in-Cambodia\" width=\"748\" height=\"561\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1815\" src=\"http://roamingclan.com/wp-content/uploads/a-woman-greeting-the-monks-with-sompeyar.jpg\" alt=\"things-to-do-in-Cambodia, etiquettes-of-Cambodia, monks-of-Cambodia\" width=\"543\" height=\"240\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times,serif\">For people who are used to wearing short dresses and shorts, it is a very different kind of experience, something that is elegant in its own way.</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times,serif\"> Now knowing how easy and simple it is to be in Cambodia, one would definitely pay a visit to this extremely beautiful place, won\'t you?</span>\r\n</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt\"> #Cambodia #sompeyar #sampot #Vietnam #Thailand #etiquettes #dresses #Cambodianpeople #Asiancountries</span>','Dressing and Etiquettes - CAMBODIA STYLE','','private','closed','closed','','cambodias-dresses-and-manners','','','2017-01-21 17:18:41','2017-01-21 17:18:41','',0,'http://roamingclan.com/?p=1671',0,'post','',0),(1682,16,'2016-12-09 20:14:30','2016-12-09 20:14:30','<p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times,serif;font-size: 36pt\"><strong><u>D</u></strong><strong><u>ressing</u></strong><strong><u> and Etiquettes File </u></strong><strong><u>-CAMBODIA STYLE </u></strong><strong><u>!</u></strong></span></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt\"><em>Every country has its own culture, be it for food, clothing, songs, language,