an.com/?post_type=shop_order&#038;p=1975',0,'shop_order','',1),(1983,1,'2017-05-02 10:56:55','2017-05-02 10:56:55','[vc_row][vc_column css=\".vc_custom_1476345679035{padding-left: 70px !important;}\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1493722687703{padding-right: 30px !important;padding-left: 30px !important;}\"]\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt; color: #ffa452;\">I’m Priyanka. Roaming Clan is my dream project. A project aimed at connecting solo travellers and assisting them in exploring the planet.</span></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; color: #ffa452;\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1986\" src=\"http://roamingclan.com/wp-content/uploads/IMG_3959-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; color: #333333;\">I quit my corporate job as full time IT consultant and became a full-time traveller in my quest to see the world. I had not clue what I was signing up for, but I knew I had a passion for travelling. I decided to challenge myself and abandon the superficial life of malls and skyscrapers despite my nervous apprehension.</span></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; color: #333333; font-size: 12pt;\">Each and every destination I travelled to gave me perspective and vision. The experience of working in the NGO’s in the Himalayas, climbing mountains in South East Asia, exploring Australia’s beaches, and volunteering in Europe while backpacking all gave me a renewed perspective into myself. I was not interested in just ticking off places where I had visited. That was not my idea of travelling. I wanted to understand the human element in various parts of the world.</span></p>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column css=\".vc_custom_1476345679035{padding-left: 70px !important;}\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1493722820334{padding-right: 30px !important;padding-left: 30px !important;}\"]\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; color: #333333;\">During my travel, I realised that no matter where you go, or what the culture and lifestyle might be, people are pretty much all the same. Anywhere and everywhere I went people welcomed me with open arms. They shared their stories, shared their life experiences, helped me when I screwed up and laughed with me later :).</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; color: #333333;\">It hasn\'t been an easy path but it has been a fascinating one. I want to share what I have seen, learned, and experienced in this journey. I want to share it with the world.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; color: #ffa452; font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>Roaming Clan is about breaking the mental barrier of travelling solo. It’s about encouraging people to step out of their comfort zone, to meet new people and to experience different destinations with a group of like-minded strangers. The underlying purpose of Roaming Clan is to convert vacationers into true travellers. We will give them a pulsating experience off the tourist path, connecting them with nature, culture, and traditions of the places that we visit.</strong></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; color: #333333;\">Our trips are not just another destination on a list but the deliberate exploration of the unexplored.</span></p>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]','Our Story','','inherit','closed','closed','','11-autosave-v1','','','2017-05-02 10:56:55','2017-05-02 10:56:55','',11,'http://roamingclan.com/11-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1984,1,'2017-04-27 11:15:46','2017-04-27